.TH "kvm_mips_build_exit" 9 "kvm_mips_build_exit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kvm_mips_build_exit \- Assemble common guest exit handler.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" kvm_mips_build_exit
.BI "(void *addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
Address to start writing code.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Assemble the generic guest exit handling code. This is called by the
exception vectors (generated by \fBkvm_mips_build_exception\fP), and calls
\fBkvm_mips_handle_exit\fP, then either resumes the guest or returns to the host
depending on the return value.
.SH "RETURN"
Next address after end of written function.
